          "message": {
            "text": "The data is untrusted because it originates from the pull request event payload (github.event.pull_request.head.sha), which is controlled by the PR author. Since the workflow is triggered by 'pull_request_target', this value is user-controlled and used in the checkout step with elevated privileges."
          },
          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": {
                "text": "Either (a) switch to the 'pull_request' trigger (which does not expose secrets but is sandboxed) so untrusted code can be safely checked out, or (b) if 'pull_request_target' is required, never check out the PR contributor's code. Separate sensitive steps (that need secrets) from code-execution steps into distinct workflows. If both are needed, use a two-workflow pattern: a first workflow with 'pull_request' that uploads artifacts, and a second workflow with 'pull_request_target' + 'workflow_run' that only downloads those artifacts."
              },
