        {
          "message": {
            "text": "The workflow uses 'pull_request_target' with 'actions/checkout' pointing to the untrusted fork's HEAD SHA (github.event.pull_request.head.sha). This creates a 'pwn request' vulnerability: the workflow runs in the context of the target repository (with write permissions and access to secrets) but executes code supplied by the fork author. An attacker can submit a PR with malicious content that runs with elevated privileges."
          },
          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": {
                "text": "Either switch the trigger from 'pull_request_target' to 'pull_request' (which has only read permissions and no secret access), or remove the checkout of the PR head SHA entirely. If you must use 'pull_request_target', never check out the fork's code directly."
